All process equipment and piping are designed according to ASME standards.  All ASME vessels are equipped with pressure relief valves that vent to the Ammonia Dilution Tank at 250 psig or 300 psig, depending on location in the system.

ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION PROGRAM 

Haliburton International Foods has developed an accidental release prevention program for compliance with the EPA RMP regulation.  The program includes but is not limited to the following elements:

- Safety information regarding the chemical hazards, and operating and technical specifications for the equipment;
- Written procedures for operating and maintaining the processes;
- Training for personnel involved with system operations and maintenance;
- Audit procedures for ensuring that the programs are being implemented in accordance to the regulations;
- Written procedures for managing system changes and startup of a modified process;
- Investigating releases and near misses and implementing measures to prevent recurrence;
- Written procedures for conducting hot work on or near the regulated processes;
- Contractor management policies to ensure contract employee safety while on facility premises; and
- Employee involvement in program development and implementation.

In addition, engineering controls have been implemented to reduce the chance of an accidental release to the environment.  These are comprised of equipment monitoring systems and safety cutouts to shut off the equipment when operating parameters exceed safe operating limits.  Relief valves on pressurized ammonia vessels prevent equipment rupture in the event of overpressurization.  Regular inspections and tests are performed to ensure these controls are in good working order.


